pageContext.claim: “Think of it, people had one job 21 years ago. They made more money in real dollars than they did two years ago, with three jobs, and two jobs, and now, for the first time, they have a choice, our economy so strong.”
pageContext.analysis: The percentage of people with two or more jobs has been around 5 percent for almost a decade. There has been virtually no change since 2016, when Trump was campaigning for president, and 2019.
